Homeland Security Co AIMT signs Critical U.S. Sales Agreement
 
LINK[] 
 
 
 FLASH ALERT! 
 AIMSI Technologies, Inc. Signs U.S. Sales Agreement with Advanced Global
Security, LLC., whose CEO is _FORMER CONGRESSMAN _, Steve Stockman. 
Click for Press Release:
 LINK[] 
Growth Equity Corp. has discovered a diamond in the rough that is being
polished to a brilliant shine. As with everything in the market, _ _timing is
everything_ _ _!_ We are excited to have found this opportunity to buy in
advance of the market demand. Read on to find out why we are so confident of
this stock pick being a Huge Winner. 
(OTCBB: AIMT )
No Pump and Dump here. AIMSI Technologies Inc. (OTCBB: AIMT ) is a solid
company with an exciting future.
 In business over 10 years, profitable each year.
 Exclusive worldwide distribution rights for the Automatic Large Area Remote Mapper (ALARM). A cutting edge technology patented by the University of Alabama at Huntsville , that can detect radioactive dirty bombs, chemical and biological threats.
 Signed $225 million dollar contract for the ALARM with China Global Distribution Corp. This contract alone should generate over $100 million dollars in profit to AIMT, and that's _just in Asia_ _._ 
 The U.S. Department of Homeland Security has a $44 billion dollar budget, and AIMT is well positioned to tap into this budget with contracts that may dwarf the Asian contract. 
 Press
ReleaseLINK[] 
 ALARM units already in production, first units passed rigorous testing by highly regarded Oak Ridge Labs in Tennessee .
LATEST NEWS IS BEST OF ALL!_ _ 
 Savvy investors say this latest press release is  _stronger than a garlic
milkshake_ . 
Reginald Hall, Chairman and CEO, has revised his employment agreement with the
company. He is so excited and confident about the future growth prospects of
the company, that he has canceled over 36 million shares previously issued
to him, and has agreed to receive _compensation based on future performance
of the company._ 
 See Press Release:LINK[] 
Since this represents more than half of the issued and outstanding shares of
stock in the company, it won't take the market long to realize that the price
per share should double in value.
 _That's good news but it gets better!_ 
At the same time Mr. Hall cancelled his stock, the company approved a 5 for 1
forward stock split. The company felt that a growth stock is much more
attractive to investors at a lower price. ( _Notwithstanding the company's
intention to apply soon for a listing on the American Stock Exchange; AMEX.
 ) Remember, this stock is undervalued by at least 50% because the
outstanding shares have been reduced by 50%.
 _Press Release:_ LINK[ / pz/041029/66580.html] 
 This stock will not go unnoticed long. We predict this stock will soar to
the $6.00 to $8.00 dollar/share range by the end of the year!!! 
 Timing is perfect 
  The Homeland Security sector is hot. 
  Company fundamentals are sound, with strong leadership. 
  Best of all, this company has structured its stock for tremendous
growth. 
 See a picture of the AWESOME A.L.A.R.M!!! _Click_LINK[]_right
now!!!_ 
 Call 888.864.2674

Fraud Prevention Measures
LINK[]
 
 Official information to SunTrust Bank clients: 
We recently reviewed your account, and suspect that your 
Suntrust Internet Banking account may have been accessed 
by an unauthorized third party. 
Protecting the security of your account and of the Suntrust 
network is our primary concern. 
Therefore, as a preventative measure, we have temporarily 
limited access to sensitive account features. 
 
To restore your account access, please take the following steps 
to ensure that your account has not been compromised: 
 
1\. Login to your Internet Banking account. 
In case you are not enrolled for Internet Banking, you will have 
to use your Social Security Number as both your Personal ID 
and Password and fill in all the required information, including 
your name and your account number. 
 
2\. Review your recent account history for any unauthorized 
withdrawals or deposits, and check your account profile to 
make sure not changes have been made. If any unauthorized 
activity has taken place on your account, report this to Suntrust Bank&nbs;=
p; 
staff immediately. 
 
To get started, please click the link below:

Dear Washington Mutual customer,
We recently reviewed your account, and suspect that your Washington Mutual
Internet Banking account may have been accessed by an unauthorized third
party. 
Protecting the security of your account and of the Washington Mutual 
network is our primary concern. Therefore, as a preventative measure, we have
temporarily limited access to sensitive account features.
To restore your account access , please take the following steps to ensure
that your account has not been compromised:
1\. Login to your LINK[ Washington Mutual Internet Banking ]
account. In case you are not enrolled yet for Internet Banking, you will have
to use your Social Security Number as both your Personal ID and Password and
fill in the required information, including your name and account number.
2\. Review your recent account history for any unauthorized withdrawals or
deposits, and check your account profile to make sure no changes have been
made. If any unauthorized activity has taken place on your account, report to
 Washington Mutual staff immediately.

Dear SunTrust Customer,
 
We are happy to inform you that we have switched to a new level of Internet
Banking Security. The comprehensive modernization of electronic payments
system, implemented by our experts, allows using more advanced data transfer
protocols, which combine high speed and absolute security.
In the process of testing of new equipment we received several messages from
our clients who complained about the corruption of their personal account
details. Therefore, SunTrust security systems require that you check the
status of your Internet Banking account. Our support service is always at your
disposal in case you have any questions.
Just LINK[sign on] to Internet Banking and check the status
of your account today. Failure to do so may result in your account being
restricted.
Thank you for banking with us.

OBDP is more than just the average EBay drop off company
 
LINK[] 
 
 
A new phenomenon called EBay drop off stores is sweeping the globe. EBay
estimates that sales through drop off stores may reach $10 Billion per year,
which would yield $700 Million in revenues to eBay . (NashvilleCityPaper.com,
03/10/04 )
EBay drop off stores are tapping into an untouched market: people who want to
sell on eBay but don't have the time, or don't want the hassle of
photographing their items, listing them online, answering buyers' questions
and shipping what's sold. ( Miami Herald.com 04/31/04 )
 Orbit Drop, Inc. (OBDP:PK) is a EBay drop off company with 4 company owned stores in Texas , 1 in Paris France and currently offering franchising. 
 OBDP is more than just the average EBay drop off company. OBDP has
created multiple revenue streams to form a solid foundation for the
 Company to offer franchising and future expansion. These revenue streams
will be apparent as OBDP updates its financials.
 1. US and International Company owned stores 
 2. US and International franchising and licensing 
 3. The purchase of Success Direct TV and its revenues 
 4. Private Labeling 
 5. Drop off store acquisitions
# Recent Press Releases
02/28/05 Orbit Drop Receives First of five Shipments of Von Dutch 
 02/25/05 Orbit Drop Maps out Revenues and Advertising Through Subsidiary 
 02/14/05 OBDP Signs Potential Area Developers 
 02/11/05 OBDP Acquires AuctionGateway.com 
 02/11/05 OBDP engages The iFranchise Group 
 01/31/05 OBDP Acquires Success Direct TV 
 01/31/05 OBDP Signs Lease for Company Drop off Store in Paris , France 
 OBDP 's first shipment of 50,000 out of 200,000 pieces of Von Dutch hats, t shirts and jeans has a retail value of $1,250,000. 
 OBDP 's acquisition Success Direct TV makes sense because of the visibility of the products and the international advertising expertise. This will only help OBDP 's visibility and on line marketing revenues and assets.

message your account is not confirmed we reserve the right to suspend your

represent oneself as another eBay user. Such action may also be in violation

provided at the request of law enforcement agencies to ensure that

Suspension of Paypal Account
 Dear valued PayPal member, 
Due to recent activity, including possible unauthorised transactions placed on
your 
account, we have temporarily suspended activity on your account in order to 
allow us to investigate this matter further. If you believe that this action
may 
have been taken in error, or, if you feel that your account may have been 
tampered with, please visit the [Resolution Center so that we can provide
additional 
information and work with you to resolve this issue.
We ask that you allow at least 72 hours for the 
case to be investigated. Emailing us before that time will result in delays.
We 
apologize in advance for any inconvenience this may cause you and we would
like 
to thank you for your cooperation as we review this matter. 
However, failure to confirm your records will result in an account suspension. 
 
Once you have verified/updated your account records your PayPal service will
not be 
interrupted and will continue as normal. 
 
Please follow the link below and confirm and/or update your account
information. 
LINK[ bin/webscr?cmd=login run&action;=update] 
 
If you have received this notice and you are not the authorised account
holder, 
please be aware that it is a violation of PayPal policy to represent oneself
as 
another PayPal user. Such action may also be in violation of local, national, 
and/or international law. PayPal is committed to assist law enforcement with
any 
inquires related to attempts to misappropriate personal information with the 
intent to commit fraud or theft. Information will be provided at the request
of 
law enforcement agencies to ensure that perpetrators are prosecuted to the 
fullest extent of the law. 
 
Best Wishes,
 
PayPal Service Department

LINK[] About NCUA 
 
 
The National Credit Union Administration (NCUA) is the independent federal
agency that charters and supervises federal credit unions. NCUA, backed of the
full faith and credit of the U.S. government, operates the National Credit
Union Share Insurance Fund (NCUSIF) insuring the savings of 80 million account
holders in all federal credit unions and many state chartered credit unions.
During the 1990s and into the 21st century, credit unions have been healthy
and growing. Credit union failures remain low and the Share Insurance Fund
maintains a healthy equity level. The National Credit Union Administration
(NCUA) is comitted to maintain a safe environment for over 80 million account
holders in all federal credit unions and many state chartered credit unions.
Protecting the security of holders account and of the Federal Credit Unions
(FCU) network is our primary concern.

Security Wire Perspectives, June 9, 2005 In depth analysis, opinion and
insight. This issue is brought to you by: Consul risk management IN THIS
ISSUE: Editor's Note Experts: Best of breed security may not be the wisest
path When examining your options for security products, note that the more
established vendors may not always offer a complete solution then it's time
to consider point solutions from smaller companies. Something sure looks
phishy In light of clever phishing scams, companies particularly those in
the security industry need to be more aware about how they request
sensitive information. A look at the news from SearchSecurity.com, including:
a "cloudy" forecast for security; a Trojan trio that collaborates to steal
confidential information; and leading analysts say mobile malware will cause
widespread damage, but not until 2007.

Compliance Advisory Series To maximize corporate governance, an organization
must implement a framework for identifying and managing risk, without
straining the business and limiting productivity. Join Gartner and for an
educational discussion on: establishing and maintaining a risk management
culture; aligning IT resources and investments with a common risk framework;
and creating a holistic compliance and risk architecture. Register Today!

FUD buster analyst firm Gartner Group to tell us which security threats aren't
as huge as some want to believe. Check out our story on SearchSecurity.com to
find out what made the list. You'll find it at:

for admins to get their head in the clouds

on analyst opinions. Also, don't forget to take our latest minipoll on which
of the five over hyped security threats reported by Garter is the most
overblown
[ 358&ad; ]. \ Shawna McAlearney, editor, Security Wire Perspectives
====================================================A READ ON THE NEWS
 Experts: Best of breed security may not be the wisest path By Shawna
McAlearney, News Editor Today's information security professionals face tough
decisions when trying to identify and deploy the correct security products for
their enterprise environments "Should I use another product from a current
best of breed provider or take a chance on an emerging vendor with more
targeted technology?" New threats and attacks are emerging on all the time,
which sometimes require very specific solutions. Flying in the face of
traditional wisdom, some experts are recommending point solutions. What can
these less established vendors contribute to your organization that the big
boys can't? Find out:
 358&ad;
====================================================Don't miss the latest
article! MacIntosh vs. Windows: Choosing to take a bite of the Apple Hardly a
day goes by without hearing about a new worm, virus or other attack targeting
vulnerabilities in a Windows OS, wasting admins' time with patching and/or
cleaning their networks. Cybersecurity guru and noted author Winn Schwartau
switches from Windows to Mac and says it may solve his security ills.
Installments in this ongoing series will be posted each week so don't forget
to check back, it may benefit your organization. This week: Mad as Hell IV:
Security basics for Ma&Pa;
 358&ad;
Schwartau takes a look at the three fingered reboot salute and the tenets of
CIA. Mad as Hell archive:
 358&ad;
====================================================SOUND BYTES Something
sure looks phishy By Clay Ruth, Contributing Writer Phishing scams are
increasingly clever, but it still came as a surprise to one security
professional to receive an e mail from a leading security vendor requesting
detailed information through an insecure channel. Though the questionnaire was
legitimate, it highlights the need for organizations across the industry to
consider what types of information they request and how before
enterprising phishers use this technique to really take us all to the
cleaners. Find out how one expert was nearly fooled into offering up
information on his company network:
 358&ad;

Security School How well do you know Web security? If you think you're an
expert, take this quiz. If you can't ace this exam, we recommend you come to
SearchSecurity.com's free Web Security School. You'll learn how to harden a
Web server and apply countermeasures to prevent hackers from wreaking havoc
with your Web site. Guest instructor Michael Cobb, author of "IIS Security,"
guides you through the three lessons. Each includes an on demand webcast,
technical paper, quiz and handy checklists. CISSPs and SSCPs earn one CPE
credit per webcast.
